{"lemma":"غَرامِ","slug":"غَرامِ","root":"غ.ر.م","root_slug":"غ-ر-م","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-ر-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"غَرام","root":"غرم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n31751"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"infatuation, ardent desire, passion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"entanglement","tags":["archaic"],"examples":[{"text":"وَعِبَادُ الرَّحْمَٰنِ الَّذِينَ يَمْشُونَ عَلَى الْأَرْضِ هَوْنًا وَإِذَا خَاطَبَهُمُ الْجَاهِلُونَ قَالُوا سَلَامًا (63) وَالَّذِينَ يَبِيتُونَ لِرَبِّهِمْ سُجَّدًا وَقِيَامًا (64) وَالَّذِينَ يَقُولُونَ رَبَّنَا اصْرِفْ عَنَّا عَذَابَ جَهَنَّمَ ۖ إِنَّ عَذَابَهَا كَانَ غَرَامًا (65) إِنَّهَا سَاءَتْ مُسْتَقَرًّا وَمُقَامًا (66)","english":"63 The worshippers of the Most Merciful, who walk composedly on the earth and whenever the ignorant speak to them, they say, \"Peace be upon you\"; 64 who, for their Lord, stay up bowing and rising; 65 who say, \"Lord, Direct away from us the torment of Gehenna: its torment is an entanglement! 66 It is the worst dwelling-place and abode!\""}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gram (unit of mass)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From French gramme."},"ipa":["/ɣa.raːm/","/ɣraːm/","/ɡraːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n31751","headword_ar":"غَرَامٌ","root":"grm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing from which one is unable to free himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as cleaves fast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(BA and Jel in xxv. 66.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lasting evil."},{"kind":"text","t